üìò Compliance Audit ‚Äì Session 3
(Security Evaluation, Evaluation Process, Assurance Levels, Methodology)

üîπ BASIC LEVEL MCQs (10)
1. Security evaluation primarily focuses on:
A. Improving system performance
B. Assessing effectiveness of security controls
C. Detecting active cyber-attacks
D. Increasing system availability

2. The main goal of security evaluation is to provide:
A. Compliance penalties
B. Assurance to stakeholders
C. System automation
D. Network segmentation

3. Evaluation process helps an organization to:
A. Eliminate all risks
B. Identify gaps in implemented controls
C. Replace security tools
D. Avoid documentation

4. Security evaluation is MOST closely related to:
A. Software development lifecycle
B. Compliance and audit activities
C. Marketing strategy
D. Incident response only

5. Evaluation phases are generally performed in:
A. Random order
B. Predefined structured sequence
C. Reverse order
D. Parallel without dependency

6. Assurance in security evaluation means:
A. Guarantee of zero incidents
B. Confidence level on security posture
C. Availability of backups
D. Deployment of security tools

7. Higher assurance levels indicate:
A. Lower confidence
B. Increased evaluation rigor
C. Fewer evaluation activities
D. Reduced documentation

8. Evaluation methodology mainly defines:
A. Audit fees
B. System architecture
C. Steps, techniques, and criteria
D. Incident response plan

9. Which of the following is an outcome of evaluation?
A. Penetration report only
B. Assurance statement
C. Firewall rules
D. Malware signature

10. Security evaluation is BEST described as:
A. One-time activity
B. Continuous improvement process
C. Emergency response
D. Tool-dependent task

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE LEVEL MCQs (10)
11. Which activity is performed FIRST in evaluation process?
A. Reporting
B. Scope definition
C. Assurance rating
D. Remediation

12. Evaluation phases ensure that security controls are:
A. Randomly checked
B. Systematically assessed
C. Ignored if costly
D. Only documented

13. Assurance levels are mainly used to:
A. Rank employees
B. Measure trust in security implementation
C. Increase audit duration
D. Reduce audit cost

14. Which factor directly affects assurance level selection?
A. Auditor experience
B. Risk appetite of organization
C. Hardware brand
D. Network speed

15. A higher evaluation assurance level usually requires:
A. Less evidence
B. Informal review
C. Extensive testing and validation
D. No documentation

16. Which methodology focuses on structured evaluation against standards?
A. Ad-hoc testing
B. Risk-based methodology
C. Informal assessment
D. Random sampling

17. Evaluation process differs from audit because evaluation:
A. Is optional
B. Focuses on assurance confidence
C. Ignores compliance
D. Eliminates documentation

18. Which phase includes data collection and control testing?
A. Planning
B. Execution
C. Reporting
D. Follow-up

19. Assurance levels help management in:
A. Selecting vendors
B. Decision-making and risk acceptance
C. Writing code
D. Incident handling

20. Evaluation methodology ensures:
A. Subjective judgment
B. Consistency and repeatability
C. Elimination of auditors
D. No dependency on standards

üî¥ ADVANCED LEVEL MCQs (10)
